title: For Sale:  Glock Gen3 23C
postcontent: I traded for this gun around a year ago and this 23C is in excellent condition with very low round count. It has very little wear on the barrel and after I bought it I had a 3.5 trigger connector installed by a Glock Armorer. This gun shoots super sweet and has much less muzzle flip than a regular 23 due to the factory compensated barrel system. I also own a Gen 4 Glock 19 and the felt recoil is about the same. This gun is super accurate and headshots on paper silhouette targets are no problem from 40 ft. or so and the follow up shots come quicker due to the compensated barrel. You seldom ever see one of these for sale anywhere since they are fairly rare and cost quite a bit more originally than the standard 23's. The only reason I am even considering the sale of this 23C is because .40 caliber S&W ammo is noticeably higher than 9mm ammo. It does come with 3 Factory Glock 13 round magazines and a Factory Glock case with a new Factory Glock lock still in the plastic bag. I'll also throw in a Hoppes bore snake. I would be interested in trading this gun for a Glock 34 preferably a Gen 4 or a Gen 4 17 or one of the compensated variations of any of those or possibly another Gen 4 19. I might also be interested in other high end 9mm models by different brands. I've got my eye on a FN FNS 9 at a local gun store so I am looking for a nice 9mm. Something like that or possibly a stainless Inox Beretta 92 FS or a nice Sig Sauer model.
